<ns567:section xmlns:ns567="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDD.MDD">

  <ns568:title xmlns:ns568="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Model Driven Development using UML and URDAD</ns568:title>
  <ns569:para xmlns:ns569="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    This course aims to provide a solid understanding as well as practical experience in performing model-driven
    development using a UML-2 modeling tool and the Use-case/Responsibility Driven Analysis and Design methodology, 
    URDAD.
  </ns569:para>
  
  <ns570:section xmlns:ns570="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns571:title xmlns:ns571="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">For whom is the course meant?</ns571:title>
    <ns572:para xmlns:ns572="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The course targets architects, designers and developers who want to learn how to practically 
       implement a model driven development process using UML-2 and URDAD.
    </ns572:para>
  </ns570:section>
  
  <ns573:section xmlns:ns573="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns574:title xmlns:ns574="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Prerequisites</ns574:title>
    <ns575:para xmlns:ns575="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     Candidates should have
     <ns576:itemizedlist xmlns:ns576="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       <ns577:listitem xmlns:ns577="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns578:para xmlns:ns578="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         solid UML-2 and object oriented design background at the level of the
         <ns579:link xmlns:ns579="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.solms.training.courses.OOAD.OOAD">
           Object-Oriented Analysis and Design using UML and URDAD</ns579:link>,  
       </ns578:para></ns577:listitem>
       <ns580:listitem xmlns:ns580="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns581:para xmlns:ns581="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         understanding and practical development experience in using either the Java-EE or an SOA based architecture.
       </ns581:para></ns580:listitem>
     </ns576:itemizedlist>
   </ns575:para>
  </ns573:section>
  
  <ns582:section xmlns:ns582="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns583:title xmlns:ns583="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Outcomes</ns583:title>
    <ns584:para xmlns:ns584="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      After completing this course candidates should be able to
      <ns585:itemizedlist xmlns:ns585="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns586:listitem xmlns:ns586="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns587:para xmlns:ns587="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand OMG's Model Driven Architecture and the benefits of Model Driven Development (MDD),
        </ns587:para></ns586:listitem>
        <ns588:listitem xmlns:ns588="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns589:para xmlns:ns589="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          generate a technology neutral business process design using a UML tool and the URDAD methodology,
        </ns589:para></ns588:listitem>
        <ns590:listitem xmlns:ns590="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns591:para xmlns:ns591="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          specify a target architecture for the MDD process,
        </ns591:para></ns590:listitem>
        <ns592:listitem xmlns:ns592="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns593:para xmlns:ns593="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand the mapping of the platform independent model onto the platform specific model (PSM),
        </ns593:para></ns592:listitem>
        <ns594:listitem xmlns:ns594="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns595:para xmlns:ns595="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand how one maps the platform specific model (PSM) onto the enterprise deployment model (EDM)
          of the target architecture (Java-EE or SOA) resulting in the
          system code, database structures, and any other deployable artifacts,
        </ns595:para></ns594:listitem>
        <ns596:listitem xmlns:ns596="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns597:para xmlns:ns597="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          have an understanding of the tools which currently support MDA.
        </ns597:para></ns596:listitem>
      </ns585:itemizedlist>
    </ns584:para>
  </ns582:section>
  
  <ns598:section xmlns:ns598="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.coursePackage">
    <ns599:title xmlns:ns599="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Course Package</ns599:title>
    <ns600:para xmlns:ns600="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Candidates will receive detailed lecture notes in the form of a bound book.
    </ns600:para>
  </ns598:section>
  
